⌂ MUTATION TABLE: HOUSE AFTER TASTING
Phase	Trigger (change in her chemistry)	Morphology Shift	Reciprocal Impact
I. Capillary Bloom	Slight iron-rise in blood from biting lip while unlocking	Microscopic rust-veins thread along doorframe, spreading into load-bearing studs	The house develops a pulse—low thrum heard in floorboards at night
II. Hollow-Organ Echo	Elevated cortisol—salt + aldehyde trace	Walls thin, inner cavities inflate like lungs; insulation converts to spongy alveoli	Air tastes faintly of her mouthwash; visitors feel breathed upon
III. Digestive Turn	Accumulated plaque of tongue-key transfers (0.4 mg Zn threshold)	Plumbing reroutes into slow peristaltic folds; sinks gargle	Water emerges mineral-weighted with her signature—makes tea uncanny
IV. Ossification Loop	Long absence → lock starved of flavour	Exterior clads itself in calcite scale—house “scabs over”	She must chip herself a doorway or risk permanent exclusion
V. Inward Fold	Sudden pH drop (tears) + ant-gel scent	Hallway bends, Möbius-twists; every path returns to kitchen	Confrontation: she cannot avoid the site of compromise—the ant saga room becomes the only room
VI. Symbiotic Residence	Stable flavour equilibrium (habitual ritual)	House grows palatal ridges along corridors; keyhole evolves into soft valve	Crossing threshold feels like being gently swallowed, then cradled; safety equals surrender
VII. Autophagic Closure	Loss of tongue (silence, refusal / accident)	Door seals with keratin-like shell, ornaments itself with mirrored pads	House goes feral: no entry without offering a new organ—hers or another’s
Narrative Spiral

    Containment Risk
    If she keeps adapting with the house, interior morphs to fit her biochemical story—eventually rooms echo the shape of her throat. Comfort becomes captivity.

    Exilic Risk
    Should her taste change irrevocably—new medication, grief-shift, bacterial bloom—the door’s memory classifies her as other. She watches a former home digest the zinc-ghost she left behind.

    Covenant Option
    She might forge a secondary key—someone she trusts learns the flavour palette. Shared access dilutes singular cost; house starts telling a plural story, corridors bifurcate, echoes braid.

Live Vectors

    ☼ presence-cost now bilateral & expanding

    🪞 mirror-sympathy reflected in architecture—she walks inside her own amplified palate

    ∴ simulated-ethic house enforces consequences she once outsourced to conscience

    “A door that tastes back eventually chooses its diet.”

Let me know when you want to freeze one of these phases into a formal node or if you’d rather keep the recursion fluid.
