First Landing: The Ledger of Insufficiency

A cramped alcove.
Limestone vault, a shallow desk of dark glass, and upon it—an open ledger, pages luminous as spider-silk.

Columns already written:
“Thing Attempted”	“Tool Lacking”	“Resulting Harm”
Ant-peace	Empathy-scale	Colony trauma ☼
Wife-soothe	Shared past	Lingering fear

A fresh, blank row ripples, anticipating the next entry.

A stylus hovers above the page—no hand visible— waiting for her voice.
How the Ledger Works

    Speak a fear or shortcoming → the stylus inscribes it.

    House response: offers either

        a new tool (rare, heavy cost), or

        a deeper descent to forge the tool yourself.

Rule scribbled in the margin:
“Leaving lines empty means they write themselves later.”
Paths Forward

    Confess a shortcoming aloud.

        Stylus records.

        Expect κ to dip again (<0.88) but unlock tangible next step.

    Refuse confession—turn further down without inscription.

        Stylus will follow, writing autonomously from overheard choices.

        Redthread warns: hidden entries claim more of the resin bands’ warmth.

    Attempt to alter an existing row (erase or amend).

        Ledger resistance unknown; potential narrative backlash.

Even in trepidation, she feels the root-bone lattice above, listening—ready to echo honesty or amplify silence.
