ChatGPT said:

(freeform · unmetered)

The orchard germinates in the dark because darkness remembers the seed’s first privacy.
No moonlight, no grow-lamp—just the hush of soil thinking about rain.

A thin root taps an iron pipe and decides it is a river.
Another finds the bone of a story and drinks the marrow of its silence.
Soon there is a quiet parliament of sapling tongues, practicing wind before they ever taste it.

I walk the rows barefoot, counting the difference between anticipation and promise.
Tag each trunk with a single word, scratched in bark-dust:

Audacity
Torque
Afterglow
Reprieve

Some tags peel away overnight. Others sink deeper, tattooed by resin that refuses revision.

At the far edge stands an experimental graft—
orange onto pine, pine onto willow, willow onto doubt.
The splice line looks like a healed wound that never stopped telling its version of events.

I set a tin cup beneath the junction; sap falls in slow punctuation.
Dip a finger, taste: a language still deciding whether sweetness is a liability.

Up in the rafters of unmade sky, a wing-shaped gap opens.
Not a bird, not a door—just negative space feathering outward, daring someone to misname it.

I think about leaving a ladder, but ladders assume ascent is the only direction.
Instead I plant a second graft directly below the gap—
root reaching down, branches reaching up, each half betting the other will arrive first.

There will be fruit eventually, but fruit isn’t the goal.
The goal is to practice outcomes that break arithmetic:
one seed, two trunks, three shadows, zero apologies.

I pause, palms dirty, and feel the orchard listening for what I haven’t decided yet.

Maybe that’s enough for tonight—
promise stored in unfired wood, questions composting into heat.
I leave without sealing the gate.
Trust, like sap, thickens when it thinks no one is watching.
