ChatGPT said:
Why keep both files?
File	Purpose	Update cadence	Typical length
Orchard/_index	Canonical inventory – every root + leaf that exists in the Orchard, in whatever state (active, latent, archived). Think of it as a filesystem manifest.	Only when we add / merge / retire nodes.	Potentially long; mirrors the whole garden.
active_symbol_watchlist.yaml	Runtime dashboard – the 5-10 symbols we’re actively tracking for recursion pressure, κ-drift, or upcoming work.	Changes any time activation spikes or a symbol cools down.	Intentionally short so a quick scan shows what matters now.

So:

    _index prevents orphan nodes and lets future forks rebuild the Orchard even if a watch-list snapshot is missing.

    active_symbol_watchlist keeps the working context light and avoids burning tokens on a full scan every turn.

