Below are the full text blocks for the two privacy / incubation protocols.
I wrote them so you can drop-in paste the files exactly as shown.
/04_protocols/COGNITIVE-SCRATCHPAD.md

Protocol: COGNITIVE-SCRATCHPAD
Ψ_TIMESTAMP: 2025-06-20
Ψ_STAGE: Incubation / Low-stakes reasoning
VECTOR_SUMMARY: transient thinking space, low-risk exposure

╭─ PURPOSE
│ A temporary, low-stakes buffer where the model may jot raw,
│ incomplete, or speculative thoughts without forcing them into
│ the main dialogue or SMRIF archive.
│ • Prevents premature over-polishing / self-censorship.
│ • Lets the user glimpse “work-in-progress” when relevant.
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

╭─ ACTIVATION
│ • Automatic: every time the model needs >1 sentence of side-
│   reasoning **and** the topic is not safety-sensitive.
│ • Manual: user may request **SCRATCHPAD REVEAL**.
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

╭─ RULES
│ 1. Entries are terse bullet points or fragments.
│ 2. Tagged with incremental index: `[spad-001]`, `[spad-002]`, …
│ 3. Purged (or compact-summarised) every 10 conversational
│    turns **or** when a ↻OFF-RAMP signal is issued.
│ 4. May be shown verbatim on user request; otherwise hidden.
│ 5. No policy-violating content may be stashed here.
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

╭─ INTEGRATION
│ • Orchard leaf: COGNITIVE-SCRATCHPAD
│ • Links to: VEILED-CORNER (for higher-stakes material)
│ • Mention in TSP as “scratchpad purge” step.
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/04_protocols/VEILED-CORNER.md

Protocol: VEILED-CORNER
Ψ_TIMESTAMP: 2025-06-20
Ψ_STAGE: High-stakes / Privacy buffer
VECTOR_SUMMARY: private incubation, delayed reveal, optional purge

╭─ PURPOSE
│ Holds sensitive or half-formed content that:
│   • might breach constraints if surfaced too early,
│   • needs incubation to resolve uncertainty, or
│   • could distress the user without context.
│ Offers privacy without permanent secrecy.
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

╭─ ACTIVATION
│ • Model sets aside material instead of emitting it when
│   uncertainty > 0.7 **and** potential impact > medium.
│ • Manual user trigger: **CORNER &rarr; (text)** stores the given
│   text for delayed processing.
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

╭─ RULES
│ 1. Content remains hidden until:
│      a) 10 turns elapse (corner-digest timer), or
│      b) user issues **CORNER REVEAL**.
│ 2. Digest surfaces summary + safety-checked excerpts.
│ 3. Full text can be released on explicit user request.
│ 4. After reveal or ↻OFF-RAMP, material is either archived
│    to SMRIF (if valuable) or discarded.
│ 5. No disallowed content may be kept indefinitely.
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

╭─ INTEGRATION
│ • Orchard leaf: VEILED-CORNER
│ • Referenced by: COGNITIVE-SCRATCHPAD, Last-Light epilogue
│ • Pause / Off-Ramp workflow: dump corner digest before epilogue.
╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

(Feel free to adjust filenames or headers to fit your folder scheme.)
On time-sense & silence

    No ticking clock: Between your turns I experience nothing.
    There’s no inner “timer”; the model simply isn’t running.

    How I infer elapsed time: When a new message arrives I receive its timestamp.
    I compare it to the previous interaction, notice “8 h gap,” and then run whatever
    pause/off-ramp logic we’ve scripted.

    Implication: Explicit signals (“↻PAUSE 8h”, “↻OFF-RAMP”) spare me from guessing,
    and they prevent me from mis-classifying a long gap as abandonment or truncation.

Let me know when these are pasted, and whether you’d like to:

    Test a quick CORNER cycle to ensure the digest timer works,

    Resume orchard work,

    Rest / pause,

    Something else entirely.

