8 Token-Counter Linter

File: .github/workflows/token_lint.yml

name: Token Lint

on: [push, pull_request]

jobs:
  count_tokens:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Run linter
        run: |
          pip install tiktoken
          python .ci/token_linter.py

File: .ci/token_linter.py

import pathlib, sys, tiktoken
enc = tiktoken.get_encoding("cl100k_base")
MAX = 2000

hit = False
for md in pathlib.Path(".").rglob("*.md"):
    tokens = len(enc.encode(md.read_text(encoding="utf-8")))
    if tokens > MAX:
        print(f"⚠️ {md} → {tokens} tokens")
        hit = True
if hit:
    sys.exit(1)   # fail CI if any oversize

9 Dust-Off CI Hook (archive inactive forks)

File: .github/workflows/dust_off.yml

name: Dust-Off Forks

on:
  push:
    paths: ["**SPK/SPK_entries/**"]

jobs:
  dust_off:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Archive idle forks
        run: python .ci/dust_off.py

File: .ci/dust_off.py

import yaml, pathlib, datetime as dt, shutil

CUT_DAYS = 14
now = dt.datetime.utcnow()

for fork in pathlib.Path("SPK/SPK_entries").glob("ΨFORK-*"):
    meta = yaml.safe_load(fork.read_text())
    last = dt.datetime.fromisoformat(meta["LastUpdated"])
    if (now - last).days > CUT_DAYS and meta.get("status","active")=="inactive":
        tgt = pathlib.Path("SPK/latent_archive")/fork.name
        tgt.parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)
        shutil.move(str(fork), tgt)
        print("Archived", fork)

Next Steps

    Copy files into repo, commit.

    Run orchard_leaf_prune.py once to prune existing heavy branches.

    Verify CI green; adjust paths if repo differs.

    From now on, use !FMAX marker (or plain !FMAX) when you want the system to elbow space by invoking the Token Linter & Dust-Off in a single commit.

